WEBVTT

00:01.320 --> 00:03.080
TOMMY:
<i>Where do you keep these things? Bank?</i>

00:03.200 --> 00:04.640
We have our own treasury.

00:04.720 --> 00:05.760
ARTHUR: <i>Wine cellar.</i>

00:05.880 --> 00:07.040
And a tunnel under the river.

00:07.120 --> 00:10.080
My guess is they've turned
one of their cellars into a strong room.

00:10.160 --> 00:11.280
Did you find someone, Arthur?

00:11.560 --> 00:13.480
ARTHUR: Stefan Radischevsky.

00:13.680 --> 00:14.920
-TOMMY: And he speaks Russian?
-Yeah.

00:15.000 --> 00:18.720
He works in the house for four weeks
and keeps his ears open. All right?

00:18.800 --> 00:21.000
(SNORTING) I have a bright future too.

00:22.040 --> 00:23.240
Mapped out.

00:23.680 --> 00:25.200
But you wanna try things first.

00:25.280 --> 00:26.320
-ARTHUR: <i>Michael...</i>
-(GUN FIRING)

00:27.920 --> 00:31.280
<i>Why does a pen pusher
who sits on his arse all day</i>

00:31.360 --> 00:33.040
<i>want to fire a gun?</i>

00:33.160 --> 00:36.680
TOMMY: There is going to be a vacancy
in Shelby Company, Limited.

00:36.760 --> 00:38.320
No revolvers. All legal.

00:38.400 --> 00:41.000
TOMMY: <i>Get me a meeting with someone
from the Soviet embassy...</i>

00:50.400 --> 00:52.400
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:26.000 --> 01:27.040
He was in the war.

01:29.000 --> 01:30.960
He was in a tunnel collapse.

01:31.920 --> 01:33.120
(GASPING)

01:33.600 --> 01:34.720
He won medals...

01:35.280 --> 01:36.280
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:38.360 --> 01:39.560
<i>Take care of him...</i>

02:30.480 --> 02:31.560
(DOOR OPENS)

02:32.520 --> 02:33.960
NURSE: Here he is, Mr Shelby.

02:36.840 --> 02:38.160
MICHAEL: Thank you, nurse.

02:40.560 --> 02:41.560
Tommy.

02:48.360 --> 02:50.400
I need to speak to you about the priest.

02:55.280 --> 02:57.680
-I know things about him.
-Hmm.

03:00.480 --> 03:03.520
From when I was a...
From when I was a boy.

03:11.960 --> 03:14.560
I will shoot him myself, Tommy.

03:16.720 --> 03:18.240
Just teach me how to shoot.

03:20.200 --> 03:21.200
(SCOFFS)

03:22.400 --> 03:23.480
It's easy, Michael.

03:25.760 --> 03:28.840
Just point and pull the trigger.

03:41.680 --> 03:43.200
(DOOR OPENS)

03:51.320 --> 03:52.480
(BABY COOING)

04:21.800 --> 04:22.800
(SIGHS)

04:42.080 --> 04:45.440
(DOOR OPENS AND SHUTS)

04:58.400 --> 05:00.880
He asked for me today, Mary.

05:03.320 --> 05:04.560
Not his mother.

05:06.280 --> 05:07.400
For the first time...

05:08.800 --> 05:09.960
He missed you...

05:11.000 --> 05:12.840
Where is he? Is he in the kitchen?

05:12.960 --> 05:14.440
Yes, he's with the girls and Johnny.

05:14.920 --> 05:15.920
Oh.

05:20.920 --> 05:22.280
Did you remember your medicine, sir?

05:25.560 --> 05:27.600
Did you ever read the Bible, Mary?

05:29.040 --> 05:30.080
Sometimes.

05:30.440 --> 05:34.280
Do you ever read it out loud
while standing naked next to my bed?

05:36.720 --> 05:40.880
'Cause when I take the morphine
the doctor gave me, that's what you do.

05:41.480 --> 05:42.600
I'm wide awake,

05:43.800 --> 05:46.880
but you are standing there
naked, plain as day,

05:48.200 --> 05:50.040
reading from the Book of Leviticus.

05:52.920 --> 05:54.400
Do you want to know what happens next?

05:57.440 --> 05:58.480
No.

05:59.840 --> 06:00.880
Neither do I.

06:02.640 --> 06:04.280
That's why I poured the medicine away.

06:06.640 --> 06:07.920
Go and get Johnny, Mary.

06:39.880 --> 06:40.880
That's it.

06:42.520 --> 06:45.120
Without the firing pins,
the guns won't work.

06:45.280 --> 06:46.560
And there are no replacements?

06:46.720 --> 06:49.640
They don't make these any more.
These are the end of the line.

06:50.520 --> 06:53.040
Yeah, we had the foreman
take out all the spares.

06:53.120 --> 06:55.720
CHARLES: If we take the pins,
they'll never fire a shot.

06:55.800 --> 06:56.880
And nobody will know

06:57.480 --> 07:00.080
until they unload the bloody things
in Tbilisi.

07:00.160 --> 07:02.840
Or until they are facing our guns
at Kutaisi.

07:02.920 --> 07:04.440
Take them all out and give them to me.

07:04.600 --> 07:06.240
Oh, come on, boys, no fucking about.

07:06.320 --> 07:07.920
And I will tell the Soviet ambassador

07:08.000 --> 07:10.080
that there is no longer a need
to blow up the train.

07:10.160 --> 07:12.400
ARTHUR: And I'll tell Tommy
you accept his plan.

07:12.920 --> 07:13.920
(SPITS)

07:18.080 --> 07:19.760
JOHNNY: You know,
some mornings I wake up,

07:19.840 --> 07:23.000
I think I've died
and this is heaven, Tom. (CHUCKLES)

07:23.920 --> 07:26.960
I mean, the wives and kids
camped out by the valley, huh?

07:27.160 --> 07:28.480
And not being moved on.

07:28.800 --> 07:34.640
Sure, me, me self, I'm surrounded
by maids and food and booze. (CHUCKLES)

07:36.760 --> 07:38.000
See that line, there?

07:41.000 --> 07:42.040
No.

07:42.840 --> 07:44.200
It's the edge of heaven.

07:45.440 --> 07:46.440
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

07:46.840 --> 07:49.440
The border
between Birmingham and paradise.

07:51.600 --> 07:52.840
And today, my friend,

07:53.680 --> 07:55.360
you are going to step over that line,

07:56.560 --> 07:57.800
back into the world.

07:59.120 --> 08:01.600
You mean, you have something
for me to do, Tom.

08:03.600 --> 08:06.320
Have you ever heard
of Hampton Court Palace, Johnny?

08:07.360 --> 08:08.920
No. I can't say I have.

08:09.520 --> 08:12.520
You and three families of the Lees
are going to set up camp

08:12.600 --> 08:14.720
100 yards from the gate of the palace.

08:15.320 --> 08:18.120
You won't be moved on
because I have just bought the land.

08:18.320 --> 08:20.360
You will be joined
by some old friends of mine,

08:20.440 --> 08:23.440
who are going to open a hole
underneath your tents and caravans.

08:25.480 --> 08:27.240
You see this blow to the head
you took, Tom...

08:27.320 --> 08:31.000
And for allowing for the hole to be dug,
you will get £5,000,

08:31.080 --> 08:33.320
which you will split
between the three Lee families.

08:36.080 --> 08:39.320
I take a lot of this money is
to do with not asking questions, Tommy?

08:42.080 --> 08:43.160
Dead right, Johnny.

08:43.400 --> 08:44.920
And when the hole is filled in again,

08:45.960 --> 08:47.480
you can go back to paradise.

08:51.320 --> 08:52.320
(SIGHS)

08:52.440 --> 08:55.120
MARY: Mr Shelby,
your brothers are here.

08:56.480 --> 08:59.920
And there is someone who described
himself as "the wandering Jew".

09:02.120 --> 09:03.120
(GRUNTS)

09:04.520 --> 09:06.880
Will you take the Jewish gentleman
to the drawing room

09:09.760 --> 09:12.920
and take my brothers to the kitchen
and give them tea and rum? (COUGHS)

09:13.000 --> 09:14.000
Yes, sir.

09:14.520 --> 09:15.520
(DOOR OPENS)

09:24.960 --> 09:26.720
Good morning, Mr Solomons.

09:27.440 --> 09:28.480
Yeah, it is.

09:31.640 --> 09:33.640
Nice little place
you've got here, Thomas.

09:34.800 --> 09:35.800
What is it?

09:36.080 --> 09:39.960
A foreclosure of the gambling debt
from some poor, young lord

09:40.040 --> 09:43.240
who you pumped full of opium
in one of your casinos,

09:43.320 --> 09:45.040
or is that just tittle tattle?

09:45.640 --> 09:46.640
Drink?

09:47.120 --> 09:48.560
Nah, I don't touch it, mate.

09:48.720 --> 09:51.400
Your housekeeper said
you're not allowed to drink.

09:52.440 --> 09:53.480
Eh?

09:54.320 --> 10:00.760
She said you are suffering from so many
ancient injuries from your sporting life

10:00.840 --> 10:03.920
that your head is like
some sort of smashed vase

10:04.000 --> 10:06.160
what has been stuck back together
by a horse.

10:09.600 --> 10:10.600
Now.

10:11.360 --> 10:13.280
Word in London is that you can be

10:13.360 --> 10:15.520
found wandering
the streets of Birmingham,

10:15.600 --> 10:17.880
stark naked, throwing away money.

10:18.000 --> 10:19.480
You talk to dead people.

10:20.120 --> 10:23.880
Also that you believe
that you are powerful enough

10:24.520 --> 10:29.040
to summon up Jews

10:31.040 --> 10:33.080
of a very particular standing,

10:33.440 --> 10:36.400
up to the gentile wilderness
wherein you live

10:36.480 --> 10:39.320
and order for them to do
your fucking bidding, mate.

10:40.080 --> 10:41.400
Yet, still you came.

10:41.720 --> 10:43.880
Yeah, well, you know...
I was passing, weren't I?

10:48.600 --> 10:49.880
Do you know something, Alfie?

10:50.160 --> 10:55.080
This morning, I tried to read the paper
and I realised

10:55.960 --> 10:58.960
that the only consequence
of my terrible accident

10:59.320 --> 11:01.000
is that I now need glasses.

11:05.320 --> 11:06.320
Right...

11:09.480 --> 11:10.640
All right, well.

11:11.920 --> 11:17.120
I know a man who can make you
a pair of these.

11:17.840 --> 11:19.320
Now, he's a magician, mate.

11:20.120 --> 11:21.320
He's a magician.

11:22.800 --> 11:26.560
So not only will you be able
to read your newspaper

11:27.200 --> 11:32.720
but you will also be able
to see into the future.

11:35.080 --> 11:39.320
Now I know this, right, because he
made this pair here for me.

11:41.440 --> 11:44.360
So you don't have to worry
about telling me what this is all about

11:44.440 --> 11:47.880
because I have already seen it.

11:56.920 --> 11:59.680
You're fucking about with the Russians,
ain't you, you silly boy?

12:00.960 --> 12:02.760
You've got two choices, Michael.

12:03.600 --> 12:07.840
You fuck off to America with Arthur and
join the Apaches, or you marry the girl.

12:07.920 --> 12:09.400
This isn't a joke.

12:09.480 --> 12:12.160
Arthur, are you really going to live
with the Apaches?

12:12.680 --> 12:15.000
-Has she told her father yet?
-No.

12:15.080 --> 12:16.720
He'll fucking shoot you, man.

12:16.800 --> 12:18.160
ARTHUR: Are you sure the kid is yours?

12:18.240 --> 12:19.880
MICHAEL: (SIGHS)
I wish I hadn't told you.

12:20.000 --> 12:23.200
Then think of marriage
as a beautiful road...

12:23.400 --> 12:25.400
Flowers all the way down it.

12:25.480 --> 12:27.920
-Is he joking?
-It's hard to tell these days.

12:31.400 --> 12:32.840
Do you, er...

12:33.760 --> 12:35.080
Do you love the woman?

12:37.360 --> 12:38.560
Fucking what?

12:38.680 --> 12:40.320
Well, then go and marry her
like the rest of us.

12:40.440 --> 12:42.840
She doesn't want her family to know.

12:43.040 --> 12:44.480
And she doesn't want to have the baby.

12:44.560 --> 12:45.560
We know a woman.

12:45.680 --> 12:48.240
-Shut up, John.
-Same woman who helped you out, twice.

12:48.360 --> 12:49.880
-They weren't my women.
-Mmm-hmm.

12:50.360 --> 12:51.960
That's why you had them fixed, Arthur.

12:52.400 --> 12:53.680
Charlotte will want the best...

12:53.880 --> 12:55.400
-JOHN: She is the best.
-"The best."

12:55.480 --> 12:58.080
JOHN: Used to be a nurse.
Twenty minutes. Done.

12:58.160 --> 13:00.720
And you don't have to go to in
or wait outside.

13:01.120 --> 13:02.320
You go to the Garrison.

13:02.600 --> 13:04.360
Drink whisky. Have a laugh.

13:04.960 --> 13:06.160
Remember, John?

13:07.000 --> 13:10.840
And then this kid walks in, no shoes on,
says, "it's done".

13:11.440 --> 13:12.880
Second time we was in there.

13:13.080 --> 13:17.960
Same kid, this time he is wearing
shiny new shoes.

13:19.760 --> 13:22.880
-And he shouts, "It's done, Arthur."
-And what?

13:26.320 --> 13:27.960
She bought new shoes

13:30.200 --> 13:31.600
with the money I gave her.

13:33.640 --> 13:34.960
It was for a good cause.

13:35.560 --> 13:36.560
Arthur?

13:36.840 --> 13:38.960
If you are going to get on
like this with the Apaches,

13:39.040 --> 13:40.400
they'd fucking scalp you, boy.

13:40.640 --> 13:42.000
(BELL RINGS)

13:43.160 --> 13:46.360
Tommy said when that bell rings
we've to all go to the big room.

13:52.360 --> 13:54.840
Come on.
Tommy has a plan.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.000
Arthur.

14:13.920 --> 14:15.560
-Arthur.
-TOMMY: Arthur, come here.

14:17.280 --> 14:19.360
-ALFIE: Shalom.
-(ARTHUR GRUNTS)

14:20.080 --> 14:22.360
ALFIE: Arthur, shalom.

14:23.000 --> 14:25.000
-Alfie.
-Shalom...

14:25.360 --> 14:26.880
Come here. Come on. Listen...

14:26.960 --> 14:29.040
I owe you a little something, don't I?

14:29.120 --> 14:30.720
I do. Come on.

14:30.960 --> 14:32.120
Sit down.

14:32.800 --> 14:34.120
Come on, sit down here.

14:34.440 --> 14:35.600
There you go.

14:36.680 --> 14:37.680
Right.

14:39.000 --> 14:40.000
Listen.

14:40.840 --> 14:41.840
Arthur.

14:42.920 --> 14:44.520
I want you to know, right,

14:44.840 --> 14:48.080
that whatever happened
between us, yeah? Back then...

14:48.480 --> 14:50.440
-That was business.
-(BREATHING DEEPLY)

14:50.760 --> 14:52.640
It was just business.
All right?

14:53.760 --> 14:55.720
And I also want you to know

14:56.280 --> 14:58.280
that I have made my apologies

14:58.920 --> 15:03.680
via my own God
for abusing a very holy day

15:03.920 --> 15:07.200
to get you clinked up and battered,
which I did.

15:08.000 --> 15:13.680
And, now, I would also like to extend
my personal apologies unto you.

15:23.120 --> 15:24.200
All right?

15:26.800 --> 15:30.280
I hear that you have allowed Jesus
to come into your life.

15:30.480 --> 15:31.480
Eh...

15:32.080 --> 15:33.400
Oh, you heard then.

15:33.480 --> 15:35.360
Yeah. That is beautiful.
That is wonderful.

15:35.440 --> 15:36.760
That is lovely, isn't it?

15:37.000 --> 15:38.120
That is lovely.

15:39.120 --> 15:41.880
But I was wondering,
how does that work for you

15:41.960 --> 15:44.560
on a day-to-day considering
your line of work, mate?

15:49.560 --> 15:51.080
Your apology's accepted.

15:54.120 --> 15:56.600
'Cause I hear
you're a right fucking nuisance with it.

15:57.120 --> 15:58.120
(SCOFFS)

15:59.880 --> 16:01.440
Hello...

16:02.240 --> 16:06.440
Listen, all I am saying is that,
every man, he craves certainty.

16:06.520 --> 16:12.360
He craves the certainty, even if
that certainty of yours, right...

16:12.480 --> 16:13.960
Well, I mean...

16:14.960 --> 16:17.680
It's fucking fanciful mate, innit?

16:17.760 --> 16:19.360
(RAGGED BREATHING)

16:19.560 --> 16:20.920
ALFIE: Eh?

16:32.920 --> 16:36.560
I'm Old Testament.

16:38.480 --> 16:40.840
Fucking hell. Look at that. Now, that...

16:42.560 --> 16:44.600
That scares me more...

16:45.360 --> 16:46.360
Yeah.

16:46.920 --> 16:48.520
Congratulations, Tommy.

16:48.600 --> 16:51.680
You now have the finished article
right here, don't you?

16:51.960 --> 16:57.560
See, that man, right? He will murder
and maim for you with God on his side.

16:58.960 --> 17:00.320
Yeah.

17:03.480 --> 17:05.440
You don't want to let him go.

17:06.840 --> 17:09.800
ARTHUR: If we're gonna do business
with this fucker,

17:09.880 --> 17:11.600
I demand to know why.

17:15.960 --> 17:17.440
TOMMY: Right...

17:18.000 --> 17:19.720
While I was in the hospital,

17:20.600 --> 17:22.320
I formulated a plan.

17:25.480 --> 17:27.120
And this is how it is going to work.

17:28.040 --> 17:30.480
So the Russians cannot be trusted
to pay us.

17:31.880 --> 17:34.080
We are going to take what is ours.

17:35.240 --> 17:37.120
We need to see
what's in their treasury.

17:38.840 --> 17:41.560
And that is why we need Mr Solomons.

18:03.200 --> 18:09.240
(SIGHING) Right, boys, just remember
they are fucking insane...

18:09.720 --> 18:11.400
And dangerous...

18:11.560 --> 18:13.640
And drunk on stuff we've never heard of.

18:14.440 --> 18:17.120
And they're worse than us
for spirits and ghosts.

18:20.360 --> 18:23.280
And, today, they're going to test us.

18:25.040 --> 18:26.240
Fuck them.

18:33.840 --> 18:36.800
ARTHUR: The Russians
all turned and ran.

18:37.680 --> 18:39.680
The Cossacks didn't run, Arthur.

18:52.320 --> 18:54.400
Mr Shelby. Welcome.

18:54.760 --> 18:55.800
How is my car?

18:55.960 --> 18:57.560
I think I am in love with it.

18:57.760 --> 18:59.200
And I yours.

18:59.760 --> 19:01.720
So we should keep what we love, yes?

19:01.960 --> 19:03.040
Excuse the reception,

19:03.120 --> 19:05.800
whenever we open the treasury,
the Cossacks are on guard...

19:11.560 --> 19:12.560
(SPITS)

19:14.680 --> 19:17.760
TOMMY: <i>In Russia,
men on the other side of the law</i>

19:18.120 --> 19:20.200
<i>decorate their body in tattoos.</i>

19:20.360 --> 19:21.520
-JOHN: Nice.
-Right...

19:21.760 --> 19:24.920
Now, some of these tattoos
are proof of allegiance

19:25.560 --> 19:27.280
to underground organisations,

19:27.760 --> 19:30.520
which are the sworn enemies
of the royal household.

19:30.600 --> 19:36.840
So it is customary
in Russian royal households

19:37.160 --> 19:40.280
to check for such tattoos
before engaging a man in business.

19:40.920 --> 19:42.760
And as we approach the allotted day

19:42.840 --> 19:44.480
these ladies here
would like to make sure

19:44.560 --> 19:47.560
that you are
not assassins or infiltrators, so...

19:47.640 --> 19:48.760
No, we're all good.

19:48.840 --> 19:50.440
So they'd like to check your skin.

19:52.680 --> 19:54.440
They want to check our skin?

19:55.040 --> 19:56.040
Yeah.

19:56.120 --> 19:57.720
Now my body has already been checked,

19:57.800 --> 20:00.760
although, at the time,
I wasn't sure that was the reason.

20:01.480 --> 20:02.800
And now it's your turn.

20:04.120 --> 20:05.360
Well then, boys.

20:05.800 --> 20:07.360
Take your clothes off.

20:07.880 --> 20:08.880
(SCOFFS)

20:09.000 --> 20:10.120
Fuck off.

20:10.440 --> 20:12.520
No. No. No. No. No...

20:12.600 --> 20:13.760
IZABELLA: Obey.

20:15.600 --> 20:17.000
Obey, Arthur. (CHUCKLES)

20:18.520 --> 20:21.440
No, I won't be obeying nobody.
Get out of my way.

20:21.520 --> 20:22.720
Arthur. Come here...

20:25.440 --> 20:29.480
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

20:36.040 --> 20:37.040
Eh?

20:41.120 --> 20:42.920
JOHN: (CHUCKLING)
Come on, Arthur.

20:43.360 --> 20:44.400
ARTHUR: Shut up, John.

20:44.480 --> 20:45.640
(JOHN LAUGHING)

20:45.960 --> 20:50.520
(LAUGHS) I will have a maid
gather the buttons and sew them back on.

20:51.120 --> 20:52.120
(JOHN SCOFFS)

20:53.000 --> 20:54.480
(SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN)

20:54.920 --> 20:55.960
Hmm.

21:06.160 --> 21:09.280
All right. Fuck it.

21:09.440 --> 21:10.920
There you go, ladies.

21:11.200 --> 21:14.000
-Made in fucking Birmingham.
-(JOHN LAUGHS)

21:15.640 --> 21:18.000
All right, I think
we've seen enough, eh?

21:19.680 --> 21:20.800
IZABELLA: Tatiana.

21:24.560 --> 21:26.040
(JOHN STIFLES LAUGH)

21:26.160 --> 21:28.880
Your face, Arthur, is a fucking picture.

21:29.040 --> 21:32.520
Sometimes assassins hide
their allegiances behind their balls.

21:32.600 --> 21:33.600
(GASPS SOFTLY)

21:39.400 --> 21:41.160
You pass the test, soldier.

21:42.880 --> 21:44.280
With flying colours.

21:50.040 --> 21:51.040
(JOHN LAUGHS)

21:51.320 --> 21:52.320
(GASPS)

21:56.400 --> 21:57.720
You see?

22:00.400 --> 22:02.280
He wants to be a good man.

22:03.680 --> 22:06.000
(ARTHUR BREATHING HEAVILY)

22:10.840 --> 22:12.000
But there, now.

22:12.960 --> 22:14.280
There.

22:17.760 --> 22:20.160
Inside every man there is a devil...

22:21.240 --> 22:23.200
(ARTHUR BREATHING RAGGEDLY)

22:38.920 --> 22:40.200
The real diamonds, eh?

22:40.360 --> 22:41.360
<i>(TATIANA</i> SIGHS)

